<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1891-07-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1891-07-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="145" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d145">
                    <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Egan</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Blaine</persName></hi>.</head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Santiago</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1891-07-02"><hi rend="italic">July 2, 1891</hi>.</date>
                            (Received July 12.)</dateline></opener>
                    <p>Mr. Egan strongly recommends that the telegraph company accept the offer made
                        by the Chilean Government to pay the expenses of opening communication with
                        Valparaiso and to give guaranties against damages to cable.</p>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>